results.name: Smallest product of two distinct primes of the form n*k+1.
mathematica: Table[ps = Select[Table[n*k + 1, {k, 100}], PrimeQ, 2]; If[Length[ps] == 2, ps[[1]]*ps[[2]], 0], {n, 100}] (* _T. D. Noe_, Oct 21 2011 *)
